    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Power Cylinders - Clean, Inspect,
        and Measure - Measure Cylinder Sleeve Protrusion
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="measure" graphiccount="4">
        <title>Measure Cylinder Sleeve Protrusion</title>
        <figure id="f3350015474" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh06/h06089.cgm" type="cgm" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Cylinder sleeve clamping (cut-away)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Cylinder sleeve fire dam (highest point on cylinder sleeve)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Cylinder Sleeve Holding Adaptor</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Cylinder sleeve holding adaptor bolt</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankcase</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Cylinder sleeve</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Shim pack</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not apply holding adapters to the "fire dam" ridge of the cylinder
                    sleeve. Clamping forces should not be applied to this ridge as internal cracking could develop
                    adjacent to the shim land.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para id="s1519" count="1">Clean the cylinder sleeve, cylinder sleeve crevice bore, and crankcase
                counterbore surfaces.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the cylinder sleeve in the cylinder bore without the crevice seal.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3350015475" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh08/H08106.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Cylinder Sleeve Holding Adaptor installation</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install cylinder
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_394.xml" xrefid="t335001503">Sleeve Protrusion Hold Down Clamps</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001503"/>
                with 10.9 or higher grade bolts and finger tighten.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not "Torque-to-yield" Cylinder Sleeve Holding Adapter bolts.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten Cylinder Sleeve Holding Adaptor bolts to 55 N&#183;m (40 lbf&#183;ft).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten Cylinder Sleeve Holding Adaptor bolts to 110 N&#183;m (80 lbf&#183;ft).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3350015476" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh08/H08107.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Cylinder sleeve protrusion measurement</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the indicator tip of a
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_394.xml" xrefid="t335001503">Cylinder Liner Height Gauge</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001503"/>
                on the cylinder sleeve flange and zero the dial indicator.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move the Cylinder Liner Height Gauge until the indicator tip slides off the flange to the
                surface of the crankcase.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3350015477" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figK06/K06039.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Cylinder sleeve protrusion (cut-away)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Cylinder sleeve protrusion</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Top surface of crankcase</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Cylinder sleeve flange</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Shim</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Counterbore depth</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Measure cylinder sleeve protrusion at three locations evenly spaced around the cylinder
                sleeve. Average the three readings to determine cylinder sleeve protrusion.
            </para>
            <para>If cylinder sleeve protrusion does not meet
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_T335001501.xml" xrefid="t335001501">Specification</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001501"/>, determine shim thickness necessary to meet the cylinder sleeve protrusion
                specification.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the cylinder sleeve and install the necessary cylinder sleeve shims.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the cylinder sleeve and re-measure cylinder sleeve protrusion.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the difference in cylinder sleeve protrusion between all six sleeves is greater then 0.03
                mm (0.001 in) remove the highest cylinder sleeve and install the correct shim or resurface counterbore.
                Remeasure cylinder sleeve protrusion.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
